 \[\frac{\begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix} \right\|} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} -2 + 3t \\ 5 - 2t \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} -2 + 3t \\ 5 - 2t \end{pmatrix} \right\|}.\]Hence, \[\frac{13}{\sqrt{29}} = \frac{13 - 3t}{\sqrt{(-2 + 3t)^2 + (5 - 2t)^2}}.\]Then $13 \sqrt{13t^2 - 32t + 29} = (13 - 3t) \sqrt{29}.$  Squaring both sides, we get
